\end{itemize}
Additionally, the text explains why complementary regimes are difficult: for $\mathcal{H}>\tfrac{1}{2}$ and $\alpha=\tfrac{1}{2}+\mathcal{H}>1$, a heuristic shows “the small-scale component diverges,” while for $\mathcal{H}<\tfrac{1}{2}$ and $\alpha=1$ “the main difficulty is the lack of control of the quadratic nonlinearity in the equation for the small scales $v^{\epsilon}$.”

